Naw, I'm just joking.

00:31:56.790 --> 00:31:59.190
No, I mean even going
back onto that, its right.

00:32:01.730 --> 00:32:04.510
Our parents' generation
wasn't-- like they don't care

00:32:04.510 --> 00:32:07.750
if a Michelin guy comes in
or you coming in or an editor

00:32:07.750 --> 00:32:09.796
coming in.

00:32:09.796 --> 00:32:11.795
It was really a for us,
by us kind of mentality.

00:32:11.795 --> 00:32:14.550
We made Korean food and we
built Korean restaurants

00:32:14.550 --> 00:32:16.590
because we missed
what he ate at home.

00:32:16.590 --> 00:32:18.570
Or my parents missed at home.

00:32:18.570 --> 00:32:21.744
They don't care about stars or
they don't care about whatnot.

00:32:21.744 --> 00:32:23.410
For us, I think you're
completely right.

00:32:23.410 --> 00:32:26.000
I completely agree.

00:32:26.000 --> 00:32:28.160
Like for us now, our
mentality is like, oh dude,

00:32:28.160 --> 00:32:30.576
this is really good, let's
tell our white friend about it.

00:32:30.576 --> 00:32:33.780
Let's tell my Hispanic
friend about it.

00:32:33.780 --> 00:32:35.210
Because we're able to.

00:32:35.210 --> 00:32:39.660
MATT RODBARD: We write about
the KBF, the Korean best friend

00:32:39.660 --> 00:32:41.390
that a lot of people have.

00:32:41.390 --> 00:32:44.690
