HILLARY: Eater.com.

00:55:13.906 --> 00:55:14.360
DEUKI HONG: Eater.

00:55:14.360 --> 00:55:16.360
MATT RODBARD: Yeah,
definite shout out to Eater.

00:55:16.360 --> 00:55:17.439
There's a question.

00:55:17.439 --> 00:55:18.980
What do we think
about Japanese food?

00:55:18.980 --> 00:55:20.230
DEUKI HONG: Sick of Japanese--

00:55:20.230 --> 00:55:21.852
HILLARY: What was the question?

00:55:21.852 --> 00:55:23.310
What do you think
of Japanese food?

00:55:23.310 --> 00:55:24.851
MATT RODBARD: They're
very different.

00:55:24.851 --> 00:55:27.960
I've been to Japan a few times
and I think the world of it.

00:55:27.960 --> 00:55:30.311
It's a beautiful culture.

00:55:30.311 --> 00:55:31.060
They're different.

00:55:31.060 --> 00:55:33.260
There is a lot of
geopolitical elements

00:55:33.260 --> 00:55:35.920
between Korea and Japan too
that we could talk at Google

00:55:35.920 --> 00:55:36.780
another time about.

00:55:36.780 --> 00:55:38.655
DEUKI HONG: No, I agree,
it's very different.

00:55:38.655 --> 00:55:40.900
I think their technicians.

00:55:40.900 --> 00:55:44.177
When I see them making rice for
three years or whatever it is.

00:55:44.177 --> 00:55:46.010
You're dealing with--
especially [INAUDIBLE]

00:55:46.010 --> 00:55:48.830
go on sushi like-- you're
dealing with two or three

00:55:48.830 --> 00:55:49.520
ingredients.

00:55:49.520 --> 00:55:51.870
So you're not masking anything.

00:55:51.870 --> 00:55:55.350
It's either it's how
you cook the fish that

00:55:55.350 --> 00:55:56.460
affects the texture.

00:55:56.460 --> 00:55:59.269
And that affects the taste
of it and the experience

00:55:59.269 --> 00:55:59.810
that you get.

00:55:59.810 --> 00:56:01.615
And how you season your rice.

00:56:01.615 --> 00:56:02.990
So all of that,
like for me, it's

00:56:02.990 --> 00:56:05.370
like when I see
less ingredients,

00:56:05.370 --> 00:56:07.080
that means a lot of technique.

00:56:07.080 --> 00:56:09.232
It has to be a give, right.

00:56:09.232 --> 00:56:11.130
So I respect that
cuisine so much.

00:56:11.130 --> 00:56:14.400
I think in a lot of what I do
comes from Japanese cuisine

00:56:14.400 --> 00:56:14.900
too.

00:56:14.900 --> 00:56:16.504
And that's OK.

00:56:16.504 --> 00:56:18.670
MATT RODBARD: Got a shout-out
to a really great book

00:56:18.670 --> 00:56:20.660
about Japanese food
called Rice, Noodle, Fish.

00:56:20.660 --> 00:56:21.300
HILLARY: Oh it's so good.

00:56:21.300 --> 00:56:21.800
